<Gmap_id>0x80c35356bb2c859d:0x9092025f05579770< /Gmap_id>< text>
I have to say I love this place. I find the staff very nice and informative. One complaint I have is when we first started going the aisles were clear and people kept their carts along the walls. Recently it has changed with people taking the carts with them so they can scoop more I don't know why. The reason I have a problem with this is because I am in a mobility scooter and all the carts block any access for me.  I have to go way around and sometimes I can't even get close to the bins. I don't mind waiting but now they are leaving their carts while going to other bins. This is not just inconvenient for me but dangerous should we need to get out quickly. I would like it to be like it was before with the carts at the walls. Other than one complaint I think the place is great.< /text>

< text>
The set up is much like an all you can eat buffet with all the food mixed together. Bins are set out with items in them. You search the bins for what you are looking for. It's a good idea to know what your looking for or it can be a bit overwhelming. Most of the items are less than two dollars a pound and are categorized as textiles and hard. Bring your own bags to store your selections just in case there are no carts available. When you're ready to checkout, they weigh & you pay.<//text>

I can not state this strongly enough- DO NOT, I repeat, DO NOT go to near this "Dr"! I wish I would have given her negative reviews more consideration before subjecting myself to the absolute WORST experienceI have ever had with a Dr. But I was desperate to get a surgical consult and my insurance only covered 2 female drs in my area.

The first one had good reviews but she was difficult to get into. The second was Dr. Bhatnagar, who had many bad reviews, but was available quickly. Unfortunately,  my pain and desperation made me disregard those bad reviews and I am kicking myself for not running out of her office when I had the chance.

The office itself was so gross, and outdated without any proper medical equipment. Everything was truthfully from the 90s or early 2000s. I brought in a CD of my MRI so she could see the problem, and they said they didn't have the equipment to open it. What??? It felt like a free clinic in a 3rd world nation rather than the office of a supposedly well recognized OBGYN in Irvine.

The nurse who took my vitals wouldn't leave the room to allow me to change. She said if I wanted privacy I could go down the hall to the bathroom. Well, they didn't even give me a paper gown to cover myself, only a stained, gross piece of fabric the size of a tea towel to cover me. So I wasn't going to walk down the hall naked. I should have walked out at that point, and I will forever be mad at myself for not doing so.

Then when the "Dr" came in, she was as rude as others have stated. She looked at my pregnancy history and asked me why I had 6 miscarriages, as though I had something to do with that. She said many other rude things and treated me as though I was stupid for having gone to the hospital for the issue that brought me to her office.

Then she examined me so roughly that I almost cried. And she had her nurse hold my legs apart aggressively while she did a procedure I did not ask her to do and I'm not sure she was even qualified to do. I felt so violated and ashamed for allowing it to happen but it happened so quickly and I think I was in partial shock.

After the "exam" they left the room without giving me anything to clean up with. There were no towels or tissues, and I wasn't about to use the stained cloth they gave me to cover with. So I had to get dressed with all of the blood and goo all over me. I didn't even want to be in that office for another second to use their bathroom, so I ran out as fast as I could. I felt so dirty when I got home that I showered for 15 minutes,  just doing my best to wash the memory of that ordeal off of me.

I am still trying to process what happened to me, and why I allowed it to happen. The best I can come up with is that I didn't want to burn a bridge with her in case she was my only option for surgery. I know that sounds ridiculous,  but  I was  dealing with a lot of pain and fear from my medical issue, and just wanted to get treatment for it as soon as possible. But now I am also now living with fear that what she did during the exam may have caused more damage that might negatively impact me later.

Please, please, if you have read this far, I implore you to steer clear of this "Dr". I honestly don't know how she gets any repeat patients or how she hasn't lost her license. All I can think is that her patients might be young or inexperienced with modern medicine and don't know how a gynecologist is supposed to behave. My husband and I are compiling a complaint to send to the Medical Board, and our insurance company about her. Her behavior goes way beyond not having a good "bedside manner". That is something I can overlook in a doctor if I feel they are competent. I'm not sure if she is incompetent or if she just doesn't care about her patients well being. In any regard, she should not be taking care of any woman, especially  women who are already in a very sensitive and vulnerable state, looking for a woman doctor they can trust. She is not that "Dr".<//Review>

<review>Let me explain my experience:-

I am glad to have Dr Bhatnager as my OB and her staff was extremely nice to me. When I was at 17 weeks, I lost my mucus plug and I was very worried about preterm labor. Doctor took special care and every week she kept me under ultrasound monitoring to measure my cervical length, the ultrasound technician ( Deby ) was very experienced and very kind to me. At some point of time ( around mid of 17th week ) I started having heavy vaginal discharge,  I thought of going for "cerclage" procedure but my doctor explained me the demerits of the cerclage procedure and she wants to use this as a last resort. she advised me to take lots of rest and gave me some tips on how to be very careful. Under her care and guidance I  safely entered my 39th week of pregnancy.

For labor I went to HOAG Newport, it was a normal vaginal delivery and I was in active labor for 3-4 hours. Then I delivered a wonderful baby boy.  But my real problem started right after I delivered baby- I started bleeding heavily and my uterus did not compressed back, as a result I lost about 4 liters of blood in around 10 to 20 minutes and my blood pressure went really high and my oxygen levels dropped. its a moment I was very close to death. Dr. Bhatnager and her emergency team at Hoag had to rapidly perform a complex procedures on me to save my life. During  the procedure I was transfused with about 14 units of blood (4.2 liters) and other blood components like platelets with in 30 min using special highly advanced equipments. Just imagine How critical i was in. Had Dr. Bhatnager not rushed and took appropriate measures i might have gone by now. I was in ICU for about 48hrs and then moved to OB ward for 3 days. Due to all these complications with my health, my baby stayed in nursery for 3 days. I am very thankful for Hoag nursery team. They took very good care of my little boy. During all these procedure and my recovery time doctor prescribed me very safe medications, which did not harmed my lactation. She also gave lots of moral support to me and my family members. Which really helped to stay hopeful and recover faster. Now I am a happy Mom with two beautiful boys.

Overall my opinion about Dr. Bhatnager - very supportive, Kind, time sensitive, highly experienced to handle complex situations. She is an amazing doctor. I am glad that I selected Dr Bhatnager as my OB.<//review>< pictures>

< Review>
I have been to so many fabric stores over the past couple of months and this store was the super friendliest a d the most helpful. From the moment I walked it, I was greeted hello and was asked how they could help. They called John over and showed him a photo of what I am looking for. They didn't have it but it as it is a super old fabric however, John showed me some other alternatives and I left with four ideas. Kay then helped me pick out some the things needed and she was so friendly and she too gave me some other ideas as well. Kay even handled my checkout and I thanked her so much for all her assistance. I do hope one of these samples work because I definitely would love to give place more business.

Thank you!<//Review>

<pictures>None<//pictures>< Text>
Mood is a fabulous fabric store; their stock of quality fabrics is incredibly diverse, and it's practically guaranteed that you'll find something in here. However, it is probably the priciest place to get fabric in LA, so I recommend shopping around the fashion district and then coming here last. I made the mistake of shopping at Mood first and I bought a few fabrics here that I later found for cheaper prices on Maple or 9th. One star off for the difficulty of finding help in the store. It's not THAT big of a store (and it was practically empty when I went), but no matter where I turned I couldn't find someone to cut fabric for me or answer questions.</Text>

0x80c2b96980a90085:0xa557d7a6f4b94abc</gmapID>
<Name>Cass K</Name>< Time>
1409190719134</Time>
< review>
OK so Mood has amazing fabrics, but they have so much it's an information overload.  Even the staff complains there is just too much.  Even worse is buying in-store there is no article numbers - making it harder/near impossible to re-order products.  When ordering online fabric is received with a sticker, detailing what it is.  When buying in-store there is the tag in the end of the bolt, but it does not have numbers, just a price and hopefully the fabric composition.  If the tag is gone, the price is given based on anything they find that is similar.  They cut, put a sticker with the price and yardage.  The end.

In addition, the prices online can differ GREATLY.  I went in to pick up some fabrics today and was advised it's quite common.  I don't know how it is justifiable to have prices nearly DOUBLED in store compared to online though.

Clearly this is a business decision and not really anything staff in-store have control over, but I will be buying as much as I can online  moving forward. It'll be worth going down to look and jumping online to order, even with the shipping fee.

Some of the staff are SUPER friendly and amazingly helpful, others really couldn't care less.  Having a staff member reply to a question with "I'm hung over ask me tomorrow" is not what one would expect when looking for specific merchandise.

Some consistency would be good guys :)< /review>

I am writing this review for the NJ STORE through online sales. I had been discussing with the same representative for over 2 weeks, about a special fabric I needed. It took 2 weeks for her to tell me they won't get the fabric in for 3months !. I can understand 2-3 days to get back to me but 2 weeks for a large order over 400$ on a fine fabric. Bottom line, they are simply incompetent at this store... I ended up ordering with the same Rep. a simple Silk Charmeuse lining... I needed it immediately, knowing this the representative should have taken the time to make sure the order was correct.

Well I received the order and I was shocked, it was clearly a joke. Everything I had ordered was silk charmeuse in various color swatches and a full order of silk charmeuse. They sent the swatches to me in silk charmeuse and yet for my full fabric purchase, they sent me polyester silk! it was so hideous I could barely stand to look at it and in the wrong color on top of it. I mean this is like working at a record store and not knowing what a CD is? Silk Charmeuse is standard! it seems almost on purpose, who ever cut this. knew they cut the wrong fabric. What kind of business are they running here at Mood, what kind of people are they hiring?  This is the fashion business! time is money! not amateur hour in preschool to play games and be ignorant of your work materials.

I blame the managers and hiring managers and I would fire ALL of them!. For not training new employees properly and not double checking all orders to make sure the fabric content is correct. Its like they sent me sand paper labeled silk. its just wrong. its a joke. DO NOT ORDER from the online store, over the phone or from the NJ location. Avoid it at all cost. IT has been the absolutely worst experience from beginning to end, you bet I'm in a MOOD to fire them all!.... <rating>3</rating><Review>Clean place, good people and good cuts. I can only give a 3 though due to a couple things.
1. Overpriced, you have a shop 3 doors down doing the same men's cut for $12. But the $12 does not include the 60 second vibration massage.
2.  Appointment application system seriously flawed.
You set an appointment for say an hour away, but then the hour comes and now it's another hour away.  An employee told me that's because the system doesn't take in to consideration breaks or lunches or how long current cuts will take. So all in all the appointment application is worthless, just show up and hope they're not packed with only half the stations filled.
3.  Full house of customers waiting and stylist leave for lunch, not just one at a time either.  In my line of work, if customer's are waiting, then so does my lunch and everything else until the clients are taken care of.
If these thing don't matter to you, great, you will get a good cut from friendly staff.  If they do, I still suggest you check them out for yourself at least once.

< text>
I love this place. The atmosphere is great, the staff is friendly, but more importantly, they are extremely talented.

I have been told that they don't allow appointments, which is great if you are like me and prefer to go when you have the extra time. The downside is, however, since they don't allow for appointments, the wait can sometimes be quite long.

They remedy this by allowing you to sign in through their website and then you just show up when it's close to your turn.

I go here, I take my son here, and I recommend this place to anybody who asks.<//text>

I first walked in and the girl at the first chair asked if I called in so automatically I assumed it was by appointment only.(Not a hi or welcome) Till the gentleman came over & said it was okay & to just sign my boys in.

It want till I started a conversation till he loosened up a bit.

My second sons haircuts was okay till I seen his line up in the back. It's wasn't straight at all and he brought it up a lil to high.

<pictures>None<//pictures>< text>
What happened to this once awesome place.  I've been to the original location on Somerville and I just had my second haircut at the Herndon location. My first two haircuts I love very much and I found that the people there were extremely knowledgeable with style and we're able to cut the hair extremely well. However I got my haircut there yesterday and it is easily the WORST HAIRCUT i have ever had. I found that the woman who cut my hair Not only was not aware of mens style but she actually wasn't able to properly and accurately cut my hair whatsoever. She had missed a number of spots where she was giving me the number 2 around my sides, so I have multiple uncut places around my head. She went way too high up on the undercut on the back of my head, didn't properly cut the top portion of my hair either and during the whole process she waited till the very end to pin up my hair (i had semi long hair) so as she was giving me the number 2 around my sides, she clipped my ear many times. She did say she was new to the place but she'd been cutting hair for many years. I felt almost as if they hired her from a Super Cuts establishment. And more importantly what I noticed about the whole ambience of the barbershop is that it felt very different from the first two times I went there. The first two times it felt like this very stylish men's barber shop with extremely knowledgeable barbers that new mens style very well. This time around I felt like the entire place had kind of reverted back to your everyday cookie cutter Barber Shop. Many new faces and maybe everybody else there would have performed a better haircut than the person I had but the entire Place felt different. The uniqueness that they had seem to have disappeared. Its like they went from a quality 1 location to saying screw the quality to quantity. Having photos of hipsters and motorcycles and a cool color scheme doesn't matter if they can cut hair right!!!  However I did call their original location and express to them my displeasure with my haircut and they did say they'd be willing to get me in and try to salvage it for me for free. So they do seem to be very accommodating still and I hope the original location has more of the feel, knowledge and expertise that I noticed the first two times I've been to the Great American barber shop. <user_id>103722434645783637778< /user_id><name>randell taylor</name><time>1420881943845<//time><Rate>4</Rate>< Review>
I have been a customer of RV Specialists for several years now, from minor work on my RV to major work (new engine) I've always been happy with their work. A few years ago, my Catalytic Converter went out on my RV while we were on the road heading east. We stopped at a RV repair shop in Kingman AZ and got a diagnosis. The new part was going to take three days to get to Kingman, I really didn't feel comfortable with the shop so I called my guys at RV Specialist and explained my symptoms, turns out that the part the folks in Kingman was ordering was the wrong part. I limped back to Rancho Cucamonga and had the correct part installed in two days. I saved a ton of money and a bunch of time.  I recently had an engine overhaul done on the same RV and trusted the job to RV Specialists, Rob worked closely with my insurance company ensuring that I received the best parts for the repair. Needless to say I was very happy with their service and the end product.  Anyone who owns a RV knows that repairs can be costly, what I appreciate the most about RV Specialists is their honesty, I know that the work being done is exactly what I need. On several occasions they have steered me away from unnecessary repairs by either telling me that I didn't need the work done or that it could be delayed. It's hard to find a really good RV repair shop, and although they can be a bit pricey, it is well worth it knowing that you are getting a thorough job done, and at the end of the day, when you are travelling across the country with your family, peace of mind is priceless.</Review>

<rate>3<//rate><Review>This is not really located at Santa Monica Pier, but rather at a food court in a mall about a block away.

We tried the Teriyaki beef and chicken with vegetables. Both had good portions - you won‚Äôt walk away hungry. As far as taste goes, we‚Äôve been to other Japanese grills and this one ranks lower. While the sauce looks good, it tastes watered down. The rice was slightly undercooked/harder - half of us liked it this way over softer/soggier.

There is no organization of orders - styrofoam containers are placed side by side with no tickets beside them. It was busy and we had to guess who‚Äôs order was next - the person behind us asked if his order was in front of ours which seemed odd, but it actually was. Our order took about 15 minutes - something to expect since they cook the food in front of you.

In any case, I would eat here again because the price was right and it seems like a healthier alternative to burgers and fries, even if the speed of service or food taste isn‚Äôt spectacular.<//Review>< pics>

Horrible experience there. I deliver for Post Mates and Door Dash and this is the ONLY place I've been to where they can't figure out how to charge for the food. It's happened 3 separate times when they are not able to process the transaction after me having waited for at least 15 minutes because of how slow they are. This last time, they charged me the wrong amount and when they tried to charge the correct amount, the card wouldn't go through anymore. They wanted me to pay out of pocket for the difference. Why would I pay out of pocket for food that wasn't even mine? They rather lose the sale and waste the food then just give me the food minus the 2 dollars that was due, even though it was their mistake in the first place! I ended up having to cancel the order, so I wasted 30 minutes of my time and didn't get paid anything due to their incompetence. <Text>One of the worst customer service I have ever experienced. I went in all happy because I was finally going to eat after a long day, boy was I wrong. I have worked at a fast-food restaurant, and when the customer wanted a entree and a drink, I always made it into a combo to save the customer a little bit of money. This Amapola employees apparently do not care to keep their customer happy. So I ask the girl if she can just charge me that deal, and instead I get charged extra, which is absolutely insane. They are robbing me from my money. Okay so I get the food, and the burrito is not how I ordered it. I asked for beans and rice and no tomatoes or condiments, my burrito came with no beans, rice, and it came with a lot of condiment, mind you that I did not want any condiments in the first place. < text>
This is one of my favorite places to go to get authentic Spanish food. I love their weekend mornings buffet. They catered an event I went to and that was awesome as well. The Chile Verde pork burrito with no beans and rice but with queso is my ultimate favorite. Watch out it is HOT! But that makes it so good because you cant stop eating even though it burns!! I love it! Their drinks are amazing too. The horchata is already an over the top favorite but their Peppino "cucumber" lemonade, tamarind, and Jamaica juices are the best in the business. The best in the western region Nv, Az, and Ca. Love this place!!!<//text>

<Time>1428279589448< /Time><Rate>1</Rate>< review>
thought I found our place. No way will I go to Amapola again. I ordered a carne asada burrito, Chile Colorado (chunky beef), the #4 plate and two extra tacos. I wanted 12 of those small 1" red sauces. I was told by Edgar (man who took my order) that he would only give me 2 sauces per burrito and only 1 per taco. I thought he was joking but no. After that I told him that I would pay for more sauces. It looked like he thought of a number out of his head then told me it would be $0.70 per sauce... Wow! I can not believe that. I usually go to a couple of different Amapola's (including the one near my son's school Indian Springs HS). Because of my experience with Edgar's so obvious made up price and poor service I will no longer be going to either of the three. Edgar... here is a bit of advice... learn a little business sense. Do not allow 20 cents worth of sauce on a $23 order cause Amapola to lose customers such as you did today. You have lost your company hundreds over the next year and if you continue to do this to customers maybe thousands year over year. As we all know, there are plenty of places to eat in SB. Places like Rosa Maria's, Albertos, Gus Jr, Mi Cucina, Paco's Tacos, Taco Bender... and many others. If you don't want our business, believe me the others do.< /review>
